OL,6,FHe said Corney heard about this
OL,7,Faltercation, although he was not
OL,8,Finvolved, and went to the pub with a
OL,9,Fgun.
OL,11,FThe judge said: "Your conduct in
OL,12,Fopening fire in a public place was
OL,13,Fexceptionally dangerous and could have
OL,14,Fkilled anyone present."
OL,16,FCorney, of Cricket Inn Road,
OL,17,FSheffield, admitted grievous bodily
OL,18,Fharm with intent, and possession of a
OL,19,Ffirearm with intent to cause fear of
OL,20,Fviolence at an earlier hearing.
